# Project-local gdscript-formatter lint rules disabled for the SpacetimeDB Godot
# SDK. Each rule below conflicts with a DELIBERATE, verified convention of this
# codebase — established by a per-finding investigation (codec review, 2026-07),
# not a blanket waiver. The gd-check hook reads this file and appends these to
# its `--disable` list for files in this repo; other projects are unaffected.
# The authoritative correctness gate is run_tests.sh (headless Godot). These
# specific rules produce only false positives or flag intentional conventions
# here. One rule name per line; `#` comments allowed.

# class-name: class_name uses a leading `_` to mark an "internal base — inherit,
# don't consume directly" (e.g. _ModuleTable, _ModuleTableType). Codegen EMITS
# `extends _ModuleTable*` into every generated binding and the byte-compared
# goldens, and row_receiver.gd string-matches "_ModuleTableType". Renaming is a
# coordinated codegen + goldens + user-code + docs break for zero benefit.
class-name

# enum-member-name: enum members mirror the SpacetimeDB wire-protocol variant
# names verbatim — ok/okEmpty/err/internalError come from the schema JSON and
# codegen emits them as-is; Default/SendDroppedRows mirror Rust CallReducerFlags
# / UnsubscribeFlags. These are the cross-SDK (Rust/C#/TS) protocol lexicon;
# CONSTANT_CASE would diverge and break the codegen-uniform enum output.
enum-member-name

# enum-name / signal-name / variable-name: a leading `_` marks internal enums,
# signals, and static sentinels as private — a convention applied SDK-wide across
# every member kind. The linter's rules reserve `_` differently; keeping it here
# preserves the "not public API" signal (e.g. _ReconnectState, _response_wait_aborted).
enum-name
signal-name
variable-name

# constant-name: `const CompressionPreference = SpacetimeDBConnection.CompressionPreference`
# is a TYPE ALIAS used as a type annotation, not a value constant. CONSTANT_CASE
# would break the type spelling.
constant-name

# private-access: the linter cannot tell own-class access from cross-class — it
# flags `x._foo = ...` inside a class's own static create() factory (the SDK's
# companion call-objects all use this pattern). The remaining hits are deliberate
# friend-coupling (reducer/procedure/subscription call-objects reaching the
# client's internals; the editor plugin wiring _plugin_config into its children).
# All are false positives or intentional; a genuine fix would be a facade
# refactor, not a rename.
private-access
